         <abstract>
            <p>The present paper concerns the semicardinal quadrature formulae introduced in Part III of the reference [3]. These were the limiting forms of Sard's best quadrature formulae as the number of nodes increases indefinitely. Here we give a new derivation and charcterization of these formulae. This derivation uses appropriate generating functions and also allows us to compute the coefficients very accurately.</p>
          </abstract>
